		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=1776"><span id=>agladden</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br>3 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=agladden&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Ok everyone seems to have weighted opinions.&nbsp;&nbsp;My weighted opinion would be my troll.  I'll give good reasons for and against choosing trolls though.  <br><br>Against:  The faction is BAD.  I havent been able to get into any places other than oggok, neriak, and my home town (at least not until i worked on faction).  Trying to get from continent to continent is very hard when you can't run through Freeport to get to the docks.  Also, i noticed that level im at right now, it takes forever for me to level compared to my paladin (i'm level 18).<br><br>For:  At level 9 i was dealing 29 points of damage on many of my hits (using only axe of ironback).  I found this outrageously high compared to other classes, even warriors.  Yet i put all my points into INT in the beginning so it was in the 80s to start.   I was a recking ball in the beginning.  Another note is that i have yet to run out of mana during battle.  This suggests that DE and Erudites would not be a good pick since they hit a lot less hard and both classes can dish out the same amount in magical attack.  Also, i found that i have higher hitpoints than some warrior classes (esp of the elf race).  And being an ogre is a bad draw back as you run slow as all heck.  Trolls have very nice agi for their size so running around isnt a problem.  If you ever found yourself low on mana in battle, it would probably be more efficient to get direct mana boosts than int since it is a warrior class.  right now as a troll with high hitpoints and damage dealing, i can take on blue con after blue con after blue con without any downtime for up to 45 minutes of fighting.  I dont know if any other race can do that, but it sure seems nice to me.  When i was at level 17 i soloed half of dvinn's life away before i ended up dying.  He was a red con at the time (but didnt have the dagger i must add).  Most of the damage thanks to kiting him with the amount of mana i had.  I have not played in a single group yet as i found i worked much better soloing exp-wise ( you can look at that as a bad or good thing).   I dont know if any other race could do that, but i know i was able to.<br><br>So obviously the troll has big pos and medium neg, i chose to take the long route for awesome game play later on in my troll's life.<br><br>Note:  Has anyone ever used greenies to heal themselves during downtime? I found it works AWESOME when your mana maxes out and you are still only at 3 bubs of health.  Just life tap them away and they cant even hit you.  </p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
